I'm the current head mod for Back to Middle-earth Month.

summary: Fandoms: Silmarillion-Star Wars fusion Characters: Maglor, House of Fëanor, Elwing, Eärendil, Finarfin, Original Characters,...
caption:
Fandoms: Silmarillion-Star Wars fusion

Characters: Maglor, House of Fëanor, Elwing, Eärendil, Finarfin, Original Characters, Nerdanel

Relationships: Gen

Rating: Teens

Warnings: Canon-typical violence

Summary: Two years after the Empire’s birth, Imperial forces led by Darth Vader devastated the Arda system. A few hundred Quendi fled the system’s takeover. Among them is Maglor Fëanorian, the lone survivor of his Jedi-trained House. He has spent the past three years hiding in plain sight as a singer for a starliner cruise company. Now he is about to strike off on his own as an independent cargo pilot, unsure of what the future will bring him.

Author’s Notes: This was written for Back to Middle-earth Month 2019. It is complete with ten chapters and about 19,000 words.

For The Silmarillion: the First Age timeline has been greatly compressed to fit within the Star Wars universe, from about six hundred years to three weeks aka the Imperial invasion. Other changes made to Silmarillion material are likewise deliberate.

For Star Wars: this relies mainly on the Prequel and Original Trilogies, plus a little bit of material from pre-New Jedi Order Legends and the first three seasons of Rebels. I have not seen Clone Wars, so nothing from there will be in here, nor will material from other Disney canon. (If you’re curious, this post tells exactly what SW material I used.)

You can read “Fear No Darkness” on: SWG, AO3, and Dreamwidth.

summary: I know, it’s been FOREVER since I posted anything! Kinshasa’s lousy internet really killed my online routines. Anyway, I’m...
body:
I know, it’s been FOREVER since I posted anything! Kinshasa’s lousy internet really killed my online routines. Anyway, I’m solidly back in the USA, completely moved into my new house, and this spring I’m leaping back into fandom with gusto. I’ve joined a local Star Wars collectors’ club (DCSWCC ftw!) and I’m attending the Celebration in Chicago in a couple of weeks. This combo has jumpstartedcmy fangirl energy, and I’m hoping to keep it going after the convention.

I also now have a functional craft room set up with a Cricut, an awesome wide format printer, and a sewing cabinet. So there should be some crafting ahead! Speaking of which, the attached images are button pin designs I’ve ordered to give out as swag during the SW Celebration. So if any of you are there, keep an eye out for me.
